 (2,'http://www.finanzen.ch/nachrichten/aktien/Narrow-Trading-Range-Eyed-For-Singapore-Stock-Market-1000512552','www.finanzen.ch','http://www.finanzen.ch//rss/news','Nachrichten Ticker - www.finanzen.ch','Narrow Trading Range Eyed For Singapore Stock Market','Narrow Trading Range Eyed For Singapore Stock Market','2015-02-26 08:00:00','0','0','news','US','0','http://www.finanzen.ch/Images/FacebookIcon.jpg','Tweet \n(RTTNews) - The Singapore stock market has finished higher now in back-to-back sessions, although it has gained just 5 points or 0.2 percent in that span. The Straits Times Index finished just above the 3,440-point plateau, and now the market is looking at another fairly flat lead on Thursday. \nThe global forecast for the Asian markets suggests little movement amid a lack of catalysts as the bourses settle back into their routines after the Lunar New Year holiday. The European and U.S. markets were mixed but little changed, and the Asian markets are expected to do the same. \nThe STI finished barely higher on Wednesday as gains from the financials and properties were capped by weakness from the plantation sector. \nFor the day, the index added 3.22 points or 0.09 percent to finish at 3,440.83 after trading between 3,437.55 and 3,455.32. Volume was 1.38 billion shares worth 1.28 billion Singapore dollars. \nAmong the actives, Keppel Corp added 0.34 percent, while SembCorp fell 1.17 percent, City Developments gained 0.58 percent, Hongkong Land shed 0.65 percent, Wilmar International dropped 1.22 percent, Genting Singapore plunged 6.22 percent, Olam International climbed 2.00 percent, DBS Group collected 0.25 percent and United Overseas Bank advanced 0.39 percent. \nThe lead from Wall Street is roughly flat as stocks showed a lack of direction on Wednesday, bouncing back and forth across the unchanged line before ending the session largely unchanged. \nThe Dow inched up 15.38 points or 0.1 percent to a new record closing high of 18,224.57, while the NASDAQ eased 0.98 points or less than a tenth of a percent to 4,967.14 and the S&P 500 dipped 1.62 points or 0.1 percent to 2,113.86. \nThe choppy trading came as traders seemed reluctant to make any significant moves following the upward trend seen over the past several weeks. \nTraders also stayed on the sidelines as Federal Reserve Chair Janet Yellen delivered her second day of testimony on Capitol Hill. The Fed chief reiterating that the central bank is not likely to begin raising interest rates for at least the next couple monetary policy meetings. \nOn the economic front, the Commerce Department said that U.S. new home sales came in well above economist estimates in January. \nCloser to home, Singapore will provide January figures for industrial production, with analysts expecting a decline of 12.0 percent on month and 6.0 percent on year. That follows the 1.8 percent monthly increase and the 1.9 percent yearly decline in December. Anmeldung notwendig'),
 (3,'http://ekonomi.metrotvnews.com/read/2015/02/25/363161/turunkan-bunga-kredit-tak-selalu-via-bi-rate','ekonomi.metrotvnews.com','','','Turunkan Bunga Kredit Tak Selalu via BI Rate','Turunkan Bunga Kredit Tak Selalu via BI Rate','2015-02-26 08:00:00','0','0','news','','0','http://cdn.metrotvnews.com/dynamic/content/2015/02/25/363161/kLrH4BgBzx.jpg?w=668','Turunkan Bunga Kredit Tak Selalu via BI Rate Dian Ihsan Siregar - 25 Februari 2015 19:51 WIB Ilustrasi -- ANTARA FOTO/Basri Marzuki/ Metrotvnews.com, Jakarta : Serapan anggaran pemerintah menjadi salah satu upaya dalam memperlonggar likuiditas di pasar finansial. Kondisi itu memungkinkan industri perbankan menurunkan tingkat bunga kredit ( lending rate ). \"Kunci penurunan lending rate , pemerintah harus menyerap anggaran, agar market melihat bahwa pemerintah serius membangun (infrastruktur),\" kata Economist DBS Group Research, Gundy Cahyadi, ketika ditemui dalam acara Peluang dan Tantangan Pasar Indonesia di 2015 , di Hotel Dharmawangsa, Jakarta, Rabu (25/2/2015). Menurut Gundy, penurunan BI Rate ke posisi 7,5 persen tidak berdampak besar bagi perbankan untuk menurunkan bunga kredit. Hal itu dikarenakan perbankan melihat tingkat bunga pinjaman sebesar 12 persen masih kompetitif. Dia berharap, penurunan BI Rate ini membuat pemerintah tidak lagi menekan Bank Indonesia (BI) untuk menurunkan BI rate yang saat ini berada di posisi 7,5 persen. Gundy menjelaskan, dalam menurunkan suku bunga kredit perbankan tidak melulu melalui BI rate, di mana seharusnya pemerintah bisa berkoordinasi dengan Otoritas Jasa Keuangan (OJK) dalam menurunkan suku bunga kredit dan pinjaman. Khususnya di sektor infrastruktur dan properti yang mendukung program pembangunan pemerintah. \" Lending rate untuk infrastruktur dan properti itu tergantung dari pendapatan bunga dan permintaan kredit,\" tegas dia. Walaupun BI sangat sulit menurunkan suku bunga perbankan, lanjut dia, BI memiliki ruang dalam memacu industri perbankan melipatgandakan kredit produktifnya dengan menurunkan bunga Depocit Facility. AHL '),
 (4,'http://ekonomi.metrotvnews.com/read/2015/02/25/363111/2018-fed-fund-rate-diprediksi-3-5','ekonomi.metrotvnews.com','','','2018, Fed Fund Rate Diprediksi 3,5%','2018, Fed Fund Rate Diprediksi 3,5%','2015-02-26 08:00:00','0','0','news','','0','http://cdn.metrotvnews.com/dynamic/content/2015/02/25/363111/3RrPN4oRCq.jpg?w=668','2018, Fed Fund Rate Diprediksi 3,5% Dian Ihsan Siregar - 25 Februari 2015 18:36 WIB The Fed. AFP/Karen Bleier Metrotvnews.com, Jakarta: Ekonom DBS Group Research Gundy Cahyadi memprediksi bank sentral Amerika Serikat (AS) atau The Fed akan menaikkan suku bunganya mencapai 3,5 persen di tahun 2018. \"Kita melihat triwulan IV di tahun ini, Fed akan naikkan suku bunganya. Tiga tahun ke depan Fed Rate bisa ke 3,5 persen atau bisa naik sekitar 300 basis points (bps),\" kata Gundy ditemui dalam acara Peluang dan Tantangan Pasar Indonesia di 2015 di Hotel Dharmawangsa, Jakarta, Rabu (25/2/2015). Dia menjelaskan, awal kenaikan Fed Rate diperkirakan pada September tahun ini. Prediksi kenaikan The Fed terlihat jelas pada saat rapat Federal Open Market Committee (FOMC) yang akan digelar pada tahun depan. \"Kedepan di bulan Maret, statement FOMC mereka akan mencabut \' statement patient \', maka Fed diperkirakan akan lebih cepat menaikkan Fed Fund Rate-nya,\" ungkap dia. Pelaku pasar (investor) banyak yang memperkirakan The Fed tidak akan naikkan lebih cepat. Namun, semua itu bakal terbantahkan pada saat Maret nanti. \"Fed menggambarkan ekonomi yang luar biasa, mereka akan segera menaikkan bunga yang lebih agresif dan cepat, tapi kebanyakan market tidak percaya,\" tukas Gundy. WID '),
 (5,'https://finance.yahoo.com/news/video-aia-beats-estimates-22-022834457.html','finance.yahoo.com','https://finance.yahoo.com/sitemap/stories/1.xml','','AIA Beats Estimates With 22% Profit Jump','AIA Beats Estimates With 22% Profit Jump - Yahoo Finance','2015-02-26 17:23:00','0','1','blogs','US','0','https://s.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/6rik6AZwuPGCiADf_9dhPQ--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3M7cT03NTt3PTYwMA--/http://l.yimg.com/os/mit/media/m/social/images/social_default_logo-1481777.png','(Bloomberg) -- AIA Group Ltd., the third-largest Asia-based insurer by market value, posted a bigger-than-expected 22 percent increase in full-year profit, led by business growth in China and Hong Kong.\nNet income climbed to $3.45 billion, or 28.73 cents a share, in the 12 months through November, from $2.82 billion, or 23.5 cents a share, a year earlier, the Hong Kong-based insurer said in a statement to the stock exchange Thursday. The value of new business, a measure of future profitability of new policies, jumped 24 percent to $1.85 billion.\nMore from Bloomberg.com: India\'s Sensex Drops Before Derivatives Expiry, Railway Budget\nAIA beat estimates for the third time in the past five full years. Chief Executive Officer Mark Tucker has boosted the number of agents, improved their productivity and shifted toward more profitable products since taking over as CEO months before AIA went public in October 2010. Shares of the insurer have more than doubled since the IPO, outperforming peers.\nâ€œThe general quality of the business continues to grow, continues to put the right foundation into place,â€ Tucker said in a Thursday interview with Bloomberg Television, adding heâ€™s â€œtremendously excited about the future.â€\nMore from Bloomberg.com: China Shares Rise to Four-Week High as Aussie Bonds Gain\nAIAâ€™s profit beat the $3.19 billion average estimate of 14 analysts, according to data compiled by Bloomberg. The increase in the value of new business exceeded the 22 percent median projection of five analysts surveyed. Tucker has singled out the figure as a key measure of management performance.\nStock Rally The markets that AIA operates in will have four times the total population, twice the urban residents and eight times the spending power of Group of Seven nations by 2020, Tucker said in a separate call with reporters on Thursday. There will be an â€œimmense needâ€ for AIAâ€™s life-insurance products, given the low government social spending and private insurance ownership in the companyâ€™s markets, he said.\nMore from Bloomberg.com: Chinese Stocks Advance to Four-Week High on Stimulus Speculation\nShares of the insurer rose 0.9 percent to HK$46.10 as of the noon trading break in Hong Kong.\nâ€œThe results were good,â€ Andrew Sullivan, head of sales trading at Haitong International Securities Group in Hong Kong, said in an e-mail. As the stock approaches its Jan. 28 record of HK$46.35, â€œit will need a catalyst to break out.â€\nShares of AIA have surged about 132 percent since its IPO through Wednesday, outperforming the 29 percent advance of the Bloomberg Asia-Pacific Insurance Index, which tracks 24 such companies. Bullish bets on the stock climbed to the highest in four years before Thursdayâ€™s announcement.\nRegional Markets Operating profit after tax, which excludes $508 million of net stock investment gains, rose 16 percent last year to $2.9 billion. Annualized new premium, which tracks new policy sales, grew 11 percent to $3.7 billion after depreciating local currencies hit markets including Thailand, Singapore and Malaysia. The insurer sells policies in local currencies in 17 regional markets and reports financial results in the dollar.\nOperating profit in China, where AIA runs the only fully foreign-owned life insurer, increased 38 percent, according to the statement. The value of new business in China for the insurer, which traces its roots to Shanghai more than 90 years ago, jumped 55 percent to $258 million. The country is now AIAâ€™s fourth-largest market by both measures.\nIndustry sales in China had declined since 2011 amid tightening regulation over bancassurance and as yields on insurance policies became less attractive compared with bank deposits or wealth management products, Credit Suisse Group AG analysts Arjan van Veen and Frances Feng wrote in a Feb. 12 report. It has been recovering since early 2013, they added.\nChina Opportunity â€œThe China opportunity is a phenomenal one,â€ Tucker said in the interview, adding that the size of AIAâ€™s China business has quadrupled in the last four years.\nAIAâ€™s new business in Hong Kong surged 32 percent to $619 million, while operating profit in the city rose 17 percent to $905 million, the largest among its markets.\nThe value of new business jumped 34 percent in Malaysia, and expanded at least 11 percent in Thailand and Singapore.\nAIAâ€™s embedded value increased 10 percent to $37.2 billion last year. The measure is used to assess the economic worth of life insurers. It had $7.8 billion of free surplus at the end of November, an indicator of its ability to do deals such as acquisitions and add new bancassurance channels in addition to support new policy sales.\nThe insurer announced in December 2013 an exclusive 15-year bancassurance agreement with Citibank in 11 Asia-Pacific markets. It began to sell policies under the deal in Hong Kong and Singapore in the second quarter.\nAIA was among insurers shortlisted for a 15-year exclusive bank distribution deal, valued at $1.5 billion, with Singaporeâ€™s DBS Group Holdings Ltd., Reuters reported earlier this month, citing unidentified people.\nAIA raised its final dividend by 19 percent to 34 Hong Kong cents a share, bringing full-year payout 18 percent higher at 50 Hong Kong cents, according to the statement.\nTo contact the reporter on this story: Bei Hu in Hong Kong at bhu5@bloomberg.net\nTo contact the editors responsible for this story: Andreea Papuc at apapuc1@bloomberg.net Darren Boey\nMore from Bloomberg.com\nKenya Commercial Bank Full-Year Profit Climbs 17% as Loans Jump Impala Platinum Cuts Spending as Profit Falls 54% After Strike Record Low Sri Lanka Rates Test NDB\'s Goal to Outpace Industry Investment & Company Information Finance Hong Kong Bloomberg China Bloomberg Television'),
 (6,'http://www.insurancejournal.com/news/international/2015/02/26/358685.htm','www.insurancejournal.com','http://www.insurancejournal.com/rss/news/','Insurance Journal Â» News','Hong Kong-Based AIA Group Beats Estimates With 22% Jump in Profit','Hong Kong-Based AIA Group Beats Estimates With 22% Jump in Profit','2015-02-26 18:49:00','0','0','news','US','0','http://cdn.insurancejournal.com/img/insurancejournal-fb.png','Hong Kong-Based AIA Group Beats Estimates With 22% Jump in Profit By Bei Hu | February 26, 2015 Comments AIA Group Ltd., the third-largest Asia-based insurer by market value, posted a bigger-than-expected 22 percent increase in full-year profit, led by business growth in China and Hong Kong. \nNet income climbed to $3.45 billion, or 28.73 cents a share, in the 12 months through November, from $2.82 billion, or 23.5 cents a share, a year earlier, the Hong Kong-based insurer said in a statement to the stock exchange Thursday. The value of new business, a measure of future profitability of new policies, jumped 24 percent to $1.85 billion. \nAIA beat estimates for the third time in the past five full years. Chief Executive Officer Mark Tucker has boosted the number of agents, improved their productivity and shifted toward more profitable products since taking over as CEO months before AIA went public in October 2010. The insurerâ€™s new business value has nearly tripled since 2010 and share price more than doubled over that of its initial public offering, outperforming peers. \nâ€œThe general quality of the business continues to grow, continues to put the right foundation into place,â€ Tucker said in a Thursday interview with Bloomberg Television, adding heâ€™s â€œtremendously excited about the future.â€ \nAIAâ€™s profit beat the $3.19 billion average estimate of 14 analysts, according to data compiled by Bloomberg. The increase in the value of new business exceeded the 22 percent median projection of five analysts surveyed. Tucker has singled out the figure as a key measure of management performance. Stock Rally \nThe markets that AIA operates in will have four times the total population, twice the urban residents and eight times the spending power of Group of Seven nations by 2020, Tucker said in a separate call with reporters on Thursday. There will be an â€œimmense needâ€ for AIAâ€™s life-insurance products, given the low government social spending and private insurance ownership in the companyâ€™s markets, he said. \nShares of the insurer was little changed in Hong Kong trading today, closing at HK$45.75 after touching a high of HK$46.45 in the morning session. \nâ€œThe results were good,â€ Andrew Sullivan, head of sales trading at Haitong International Securities Group in Hong Kong, said in an e-mail. As the stock approaches its Jan. 28 record of HK$46.35, â€œit will need a catalyst to break out.â€ \nShares of AIA have surged about 132 percent since its IPO through Wednesday, outperforming the 29 percent advance of the Bloomberg Asia-Pacific Insurance Index, which tracks 24 such companies. Bullish bets on the stock climbed to the highest in four years before Thursdayâ€™s announcement. Regional Markets \nOperating profit after tax, which excludes $508 million of net stock investment gains, rose 16 percent last year to $2.9 billion. Annualized new premium, which tracks new policy sales, grew 11 percent to $3.7 billion after depreciating local currencies hit markets including Thailand, Singapore and Malaysia. The insurer sells policies in local currencies in 17 regional markets and reports financial results in the dollar. \nOperating profit in China, where AIA runs the only fully foreign-owned life insurer, increased 38 percent, according to the statement. The value of new business in China for the insurer, which traces its roots to Shanghai more than 90 years ago, jumped 55 percent to $258 million. The country is now AIAâ€™s fourth-largest market by both measures. \nIndustry sales in China had declined since 2011 amid tightening regulation over bancassurance and as yields on insurance policies became less attractive compared with bank deposits or wealth management products, Credit Suisse Group AG analysts Arjan van Veen and Frances Feng wrote in a Feb. 12 report. It has been recovering since early 2013, they added. China Opportunity \nâ€œThe China opportunity is a phenomenal one,â€ Tucker said in the interview, adding that the size of AIAâ€™s China business has quadrupled in the last four years. \nAIAâ€™s new business in Hong Kong surged 32 percent to $619 million, while operating profit in the city rose 17 percent to $905 million, the largest among its markets. \nThe value of new business jumped 34 percent in Malaysia, and expanded at least 11 percent in Thailand and Singapore. \nAIAâ€™s embedded value increased 10 percent to $37.2 billion last year. The measure is used to assess the economic worth of life insurers. It had $7.8 billion of free surplus at the end of November, an indicator of its ability to do deals such as acquisitions and add new bancassurance channels in addition to support new policy sales. \nThe insurer announced in December 2013 an exclusive 15-year bancassurance agreement with Citibank in 11 Asia-Pacific markets. It began to sell policies under the deal in Hong Kong and Singapore in the second quarter. \nAIA was among insurers shortlisted for a 15-year exclusive bank distribution deal, valued at $1.5 billion, with Singaporeâ€™s DBS Group Holdings Ltd., Reuters reported earlier this month, citing unidentified people. \nAIA raised its final dividend by 19 percent to 34 Hong Kong cents a share, bringing full-year payout 18 percent higher at 50 Hong Kong cents, according to the statement. Copyright 2015 Bloomberg.'),
 (7,'http://www.rttnews.com/2462059/narrow-trading-range-eyed-for-singapore-stock-market.aspx','www.rttnews.com','','','Narrow Trading Range Eyed For Singapore Stock Market','Narrow Trading Range Eyed For Singapore Stock Market','2015-02-26 08:00:00','0','0','news','','0','http://www.rttnews.com/images/RTTNews_Small_Logo.jpg','Narrow Trading Range Eyed For Singapore Stock Market 2/25/2015 7:00 PM ET \nThe Singapore stock market has finished higher now in back-to-back sessions, although it has gained just 5 points or 0.2 percent in that span. The Straits Times Index finished just above the 3,440-point plateau, and now the market is looking at another fairly flat lead on Thursday. \nThe global forecast for the Asian markets suggests little movement amid a lack of catalysts as the bourses settle back into their routines after the Lunar New Year holiday. The European and U.S. markets were mixed but little changed, and the Asian markets are expected to do the same. \nThe STI finished barely higher on Wednesday as gains from the financials and properties were capped by weakness from the plantation sector. \nFor the day, the index added 3.22 points or 0.09 percent to finish at 3,440.83 after trading between 3,437.55 and 3,455.32. Volume was 1.38 billion shares worth 1.28 billion Singapore dollars. \nAmong the actives, Keppel Corp added 0.34 percent, while SembCorp fell 1.17 percent, City Developments gained 0.58 percent, Hongkong Land shed 0.65 percent, Wilmar International dropped 1.22 percent, Genting Singapore plunged 6.22 percent, Olam International climbed 2.00 percent, DBS Group collected 0.25 percent and United Overseas Bank advanced 0.39 percent. \nThe lead from Wall Street is roughly flat as stocks showed a lack of direction on Wednesday, bouncing back and forth across the unchanged line before ending the session largely unchanged. \nThe Dow inched up 15.38 points or 0.1 percent to a new record closing high of 18,224.57, while the NASDAQ eased 0.98 points or less 