 (8,'http://www.finanzen.ch/nachrichten/aktien/Singapore-Market-Draws-Flat-Lead-On-Friday-1000514807','www.finanzen.ch','http://www.finanzen.ch//rss/news','Nachrichten Ticker - www.finanzen.ch','Singapore Market Draws Flat Lead On Friday','Singapore Market Draws Flat Lead On Friday','2015-02-27 08:00:00','0','0','news','US','0','http://www.finanzen.ch/Images/FacebookIcon.jpg','Tweet \n(RTTNews) - The Singapore stock market on Thursday snapped the modest two-day winning streak in which it had collected just 5 points or 0.2 percent. The Straits Times Index ended just above the 3,425-point plateau, and the market may be stuck in neutral again on Friday. \nThe global forecast for the Asian markets suggests little movement thanks to uncertainty about the near-term outlook for the markets, plus mixed economic data from the United States. The European markets were slightly higher and the U.S. bourses were mixed but little changed - and the Asian markets figure to split the difference. \nThe STI finished modestly lower on Thursday following losses from the financial shares and property stocks, plus a mixed bag from the plantations. \nFor the day, the index shed 14.65 points or 0.43 percent to finish at 3,426.18 after trading between 3,417.47 and 3,439.29. Volume was 1.13 billion shares worth 946.2 billion Singapore dollars. \nAmong the actives, CapitaLand shed 1.10 percent, while Hongkong Land fell 1.96 percent, StarHub tumbled 2.27 percent, DBS Group lost 0.66 percent, Oversea-Chinese Banking Corporation gave away 0.38 percent, Wilmar International climbed 1.85 percent, Olam International dipped 0.49 percent, SembCorp advanced 0.71 percent and SingTel fell 0.47 percent. \nThe lead from Wall Street remains inconclusive as stocks turned in another lackluster performance on Thursday, fluctuating over the course of the session before ending mixed. \nThe tech-heavy NASDAQ climbed 20.75 points or 0.4 percent to 4,987.89, while the Dow edged down 10.15 points or 0.1 percent to 18