 (9,'http://www.livemint.com/Companies/k97g8nUTODXDl6p8Xq07LI/DBS-names-Rabobanks-Shome-as-India-CEO-after-soured-debt-su.html','www.livemint.com','http://www.livemint.com/companies','Livemint- Companies, latest business and financial news, management trends, company results and more','DBS names Rabobankâ€™s Shome as India CEO after soured debt surge','DBS names Rabobankâ€™s Shome as India CEO after soured debt surge - Livemint','2015-02-28 05:58:00','0','1','news','IN','0','http://www.livemint.com/rf/Image-330x220/LiveMint/Period1/2015/02/28/Photos/dbs-k3XF--621x414@LiveMint.jpg','Mumbai: DBS Group Holdings Ltd hired Rabobank NAâ€™s Surojit Shome to replace Sanjiv Bhasin as head of its Indian operations after a surge in soured debt. Shome, who was Rabobankâ€™s India chief executive officer and country head, will join DBS as CEO of its Indian business effective 15 April, the Singapore-based lender said in an emailed statement on Friday. Bhasin, 60, has decided to leave DBS after almost seven years as head of its operations in the country, according to the statement, which said he â€œwould like to pursue different interests.â€ South-east Asiaâ€™s largest lender earlier this month posted its lowest quarterly profit in more than two years after trading income slumped and allowances for bad loans surged in south Asia. Net income at DBSâ€™s Indian business slumped more than 99% in the year through March 2014, the sharpest drop among the five largest foreign banks by branches in India. Bhasin, who started his career with HSBCâ€™s India operations in 1979, had been with DBS since September 2008, according to the Singapore-based lenderâ€™s website. His last day at the bank will be 30 June, according to the statement. DBS Indiaâ€™s gross bad loan ratio more than doubled to 13.6% by the end of September, from 5.8% a year earlier, according to data compiled by Bloomberg. Thatâ€™s the highest level among the 55 largest banks by assets in the nation and compares to the average 4.5% ratio for the entire Indian banking system, the data shows. Shome resigned last week from Rabobankâ€™s Indian unit, which he joined in July 2009, Nayna Banerjee, a spokeswoman for the lender, said on 26 February. He previously worked at Lehman Brothers Holdings Inc. and at Citigroup Inc., where his tenure overlapped with DBS chief executive officer Piyush Gupta. DBS, which has opened 12 Indian branches since 1995, said in July itâ€™s exploring the formation of a local subsidiary after the central bank eased procedures for foreign lenders. Such a move would allow the Singapore bank to open branches anywhere in India under the same rules as local banks. Bloomberg'),
